{"lemma":"شَجَنُ","slug":"شَجَنُ","root":"ش.ج.ن","root_slug":"ش-ج-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ج-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21774","n21776","n21777","n21778"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"worry, anxiety"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sadness, sorrow, melancholy","examples":[{"text":"بَيْنَ أَوْرَاقِ الْخَرِيفِ تَشْعُرُ بِشُجْنِ الْوِدَاعِ.","english":"Among the autumn leaves, you feel the melancholy of parting."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21774","headword_ar":"شَجِنَ","root":"$jn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajuna","text_ar":"شَجُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; inf. n. [of the former]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanN","text_ar":"شَجَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajonN","text_ar":"شَجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and [of the latter, or of both,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajuwnN","text_ar":"شَجُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grieved, mourned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamented;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was sorrowful, sad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was anxious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$j~n","text_ar":"تشجّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (L:) or this last signifies, (K,) or, as Lth says, it seems to signify, (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he remembered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*ak~ara","text_ar":"تَذَكَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jnt","text_ar":"شجنت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamaAmapu","text_ar":"الحَمَامَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajinat","text_ar":"شَجِنَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajunat","text_ar":"شَجُنَت"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwnN","text_ar":"شُجُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pigeon cooed in a wailing and plaintive manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanN","text_ar":"شَجَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanahu","text_ar":"شَجَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the usual rule of the K,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajonN","text_ar":"شَجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwnN","text_ar":"شُجُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) signifies the same as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$jnhu","text_ar":"اشجنهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(another person, S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an affair, or an event, or a case, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him to grieve"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mourn"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lament,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be sorrowful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanatoniY AlHaAjapu","text_ar":"شَجَنَتْنِى الحَاجَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanatohu","text_ar":"شَجَنَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajonN","text_ar":"شَجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the want, detained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $ajanaka Ean~aA","text_ar":"مَا شَجَنَكَ عَنَّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What detained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld, thee from us?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21776","headword_ar":"شَجْنٌ","root":"$jn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanN","text_ar":"شَجَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but expressly said in the S to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlt~asokiyni","text_ar":"بِالتَّسْكِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley; (S, L;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road in a valley:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAjinapN","text_ar":"شَاجِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwnN","text_ar":"شُجُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:) and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAjinu","text_ar":"شَوَاجِنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAjinapN","text_ar":"شَاجِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a valley in which are many trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwn","text_ar":"شُجُون"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tangled trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham pp. 761-2;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAjinu","text_ar":"شَوَاجِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is its pl.: (S, L, and Ham p. 762:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAjinapN","text_ar":"شَاجِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of valley producing good herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAjinu","text_ar":"شَوَاجِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, parts of a valley;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its sing. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanN","text_ar":"شَجَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus written in the L in this instance], as ISd mentions on the authority of A'Obeyd, but adding that, as such, it is irregular, and that it is more properly to be regarded as pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAjinapN","text_ar":"شَاجِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadiyvu *uw $ujuwnK","text_ar":"الحَدِيثُ ذُو شُجُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Meyd, L, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwn","text_ar":"شُجُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajonN","text_ar":"شَجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent; (Meyd;) a prov., (Meyd, L,) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The story is involved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intricate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Meyd, L;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has several ways"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which it may be understood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Meyd;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has several modes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manners; and objects of aim:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) applied to a story by which one calls to mind another: (A'Obeyd, Meyd, L:) the first who said it was Dabbeh Ibn-Udd Ibn-Tábikhah: he had two sons, named Saad and So'eyd: and some camels belonging to him ran away by night, so he sent his two sons to seek them; and they separated; and Saad found them and restored them; but So'eyd went on seeking them; and El-Hárith Ibn-Kaab met him; and there were upon the young man two [garments such as are called] burds ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodaAni","text_ar":"بُرْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), which El-Hárith asked him to give to him, but he refused to comply with his desire; whereupon he slew him, and took his two burds: and Dabbeh, when he saw a dark object in the night, used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaEodN A^amo suEayodN","text_ar":"اَسَعْدٌ اَمْ سُعَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ Is it Saad or So'eyd? ” (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodN","text_ar":"سَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]; and this saying of his became current as a prov.: some time after this, having gone on pilgrimage, he met El- Hárith Ibn-Kaab at 'Okádh, and saw upon him the two burds of his son So'eyd, and asked him respecting them; and he answered that he had met a young man wearing them, and slain him, and taken them: Dabbeh said, “ With this thy sword? ” and he answered, “ Yes: ” and he said, “ Give it me that I may look at it, for I think it to be sharp: ” and El-Hárith gave it him: and he took it, and shook it, and said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a AlHadiyva *uw","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الحَدِيثَ ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwnK","text_ar":"شُجُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and slew him with it: whereupon it was said to him, “ O Dabbeh, in the sacred month? ” and he said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaqa Als~ayofu AlEa*ola","text_ar":"سَبَقَ السَّيْفُ العَذْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ The sword preceded the censure ”): these three provs. he originated. (Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","L","Meyd"]},{"entry_id":"n21777","headword_ar":"شُجْنٌ","root":"$jn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonN","text_ar":"شِجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21778","headword_ar":"شَجَنٌ","root":"$jn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grief, mourning, lamentation, sorrow, sadness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anxiety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaAnN","text_ar":"اَشْجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwnN","text_ar":"شُجُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K; [in the latter of which these pls. are mentioned after all the explanations of the sing.;]) the former a pl. of pauc., and the latter of mult. (Ham p. 404.) [See a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraDN","text_ar":"عَرَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cause of anxiety."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soul's love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its inclination,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its blamable inclination:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love that is followed by anxiety and grief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 165.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiynN","text_ar":"شَجِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) wherever it be: (S, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuwnN","text_ar":"شُجُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaAnN","text_ar":"اَشْجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, Msb, K;) the latter being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiynN","text_ar":"شَجِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also. (L.) A rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"liY $ajanaAni $ajanN binajodi\n                      \n                     \n                        wa$ajanN liY bibilaAdi Als~inodi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have two wants; a want in Nejd, and I have a want in the country of Es-Sind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An intricately-intermingling branch"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tree; (L, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEobap","text_ar":"شُعْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branchlet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of anything; (K;) like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonapN","text_ar":"شِجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonapN","text_ar":"شُجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajonapN","text_ar":"شَجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) in the former sense: (L: [accord. to the K, app., in the latter sense:]) or, accord. to IAar, one says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonapN","text_ar":"شُجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonN","text_ar":"شُجْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a branch"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tree, [or the latter app. means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it seems to be a coll. gen. n.,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonapN","text_ar":"شِجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonN","text_ar":"شِجْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonapN","text_ar":"شُجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonaAtN","text_ar":"شُجْنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujunaAtN","text_ar":"شُجُنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or, accord. to J, (L,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonapN","text_ar":"شِجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonapN","text_ar":"شُجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roots of trees intricately intermingling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) [but] the primary signification of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonapN","text_ar":"شِجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonapN","text_ar":"شُجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a branchlet"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEobap","text_ar":"شُعْبَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guSon","text_ar":"غُصْن"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonapN","text_ar":"شِجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tangled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"luxuriant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant and dense, trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijonapN","text_ar":"شِجْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajonN","text_ar":"شَجْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  Also, (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jnp","text_ar":"شجنة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, [thus written without any syll. signs, perhaps fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanN","text_ar":"شَجَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajanapN","text_ar":"شَجَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but it seems to be indicated by the context in the L that it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujonapN","text_ar":"شُجْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compact in make, of which the several parts are interknit, one with another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the parts of a tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["L","K","S","Msb"]}]}}